comments.body:
New to podman, wanted to look into some internals through an open issue. Garbage risk ahead.

The mount operation appears to require read/write access to the store to save mounts information (https://github.com/podman-container-tools/container-libs/blob/main/storage/layers.go#L1220) within the store. Because of that, mounting is not allowed for `ro` stores such those configured via `storage.conf` and `additionalimagestores`.

It works when passing `--root`, under the condition that the target path has read/write access, because that becomes the main image store (graphroot).

store rw requirement seems to exist because of coupling the mounts lock file with the store the image belongs to (https://github.com/podman-container-tools/container-libs/blob/main/storage/layers.go#L480). That looks like a limitation at first sight, but there might be good reasons behind.

If this analysis is correct, error reporting may possibly be improved. See https://github.com/podman-container-tools/container-libs/blob/main/storage/store.go#L3089 for a reference of how it could be.

Based on that, a possible error message improvement could be replacing line https://github.com/podman-container-tools/container-libs/blob/main/storage/store.go#L3043 with:

```go
if rlstore.Exists(id) {
	return rlstore.Mount(id, options)
}

// check if the layer is in a read-only store, and return a better error message
for _, store := range lstores {
	if err := store.startReading(); err != nil {
		return "", err
	}
	exists := store.Exists(id)
	store.stopReading()
	if exists {
		return "", fmt.Errorf("mounting read/only store images is not allowed: %w", ErrStoreIsReadOnly)
	}
}
```

With the change applied, reproducing (as for initial description) leads to:
```
$ go run ./cmd/podman unshare go run ./cmd/podman image mount quay.io/podman/hello
Error: mounting read/only store images is not allowed: called a write method on a read-only store
```
